<p><a name="Textbooks" id="Textbooks"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Physical_cosmology&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Textbooks">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Textbooks</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCheng.2C_Ta-Pei2005">Cheng, Ta-Pei (2005). <i>Relativity, Gravitation and Cosmology: a Basic Introduction</i>. Oxford and New York: Oxford University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198529570" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-852957-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Relativity%2C+Gravitation+and+Cosmology%3A+a+Basic+Introduction&amp;rft.aulast=Cheng%2C+Ta-Pei&amp;rft.au=Cheng%2C+Ta-Pei&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.place=Oxford+and+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-852957-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Introductory cosmology and general relativity without the full tensor apparatus, deferred until the last part of the book.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFDodelson2003">Dodelson, Scott (2003). <i>Modern Cosmology</i>. Academic Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0122191412" class="internal">ISBN 0-12-219141-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Modern+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Dodelson&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott&amp;rft.au=Dodelson%2C+Scott&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Academic+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-12-219141-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> An introductory text, released slightly before the <a href="/wiki/Wilkinson_Microwave_Anisotropy_Probe" title="Wilkinson Microwave Anisotropy Probe">WMAP</a> results.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGr.C3.B8nHervik.2C_Sigbj.C3.B8rn2007"><a href="/wiki/%C3%98yvind_Gr%C3%B8n" title="Øyvind Grøn">Grøn, Øyvind</a>; Hervik, Sigbjørn (2007). <i>Einstein's General Theory of Relativity with Modern Applications in Cosmology</i>. New York: Springer. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780387691992" class="internal">ISBN 978-0-387-69199-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Einstein%27s+General+Theory+of+Relativity+with+Modern+Applications+in+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Gr%C3%B8n&amp;rft.aufirst=%C3%98yvind&amp;rft.au=Gr%C3%B8n%2C+%C3%98yvind&amp;rft.au=Hervik%2C+Sigbj%C3%B8rn&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Springer&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-387-69199-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHarrison2000">Harrison, Edward (2000). <i>Cosmology: the science of the universe</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/052166148X" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-66148-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cosmology%3A+the+science+of+the+universe&amp;rft.aulast=Harrison&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward&amp;rft.au=Harrison%2C+Edward&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-66148-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> For undergraduates; mathematically gentle with a strong historical focus.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKutner2003">Kutner, Marc (2003). <i>Astronomy: A Physical Perspective</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521529271" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-52927-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Astronomy%3A+A+Physical+Perspective&amp;rft.aulast=Kutner&amp;rft.aufirst=Marc&amp;rft.au=Kutner%2C+Marc&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-52927-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> An introductory astronomy text.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKolbMichael_Turner1988">Kolb, Edward; Michael Turner (1988). <i>The Early Universe</i>. Addison-Wesley. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0201116049" class="internal">ISBN 0-201-11604-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Early+Universe&amp;rft.aulast=Kolb&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward&amp;rft.au=Kolb%2C+Edward&amp;rft.au=Michael+Turner&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pub=Addison-Wesley&amp;rft.isbn=0-201-11604-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> The classic reference for researchers.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLiddle2003">Liddle, Andrew (2003). <i>An Introduction to Modern Cosmology</i>. John Wiley. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0470848359" class="internal">ISBN 0-470-84835-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Introduction+to+Modern+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Liddle&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rft.au=Liddle%2C+Andrew&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=John+Wiley&amp;rft.isbn=0-470-84835-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Cosmology without general relativity.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLiddleDavid_Lyth2000">Liddle, Andrew; David Lyth (2000). <i>Cosmological Inflation and Large-Scale Structure</i>. Cambridge. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521575982" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-57598-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cosmological+Inflation+and+Large-Scale+Structure&amp;rft.aulast=Liddle&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rft.au=Liddle%2C+Andrew&amp;rft.au=David+Lyth&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-57598-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> An introduction to cosmology with a thorough discussion of <a href="/wiki/Inflation" title="Inflation">inflation</a>.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMukhanov2005">Mukhanov, Viatcheslav (2005). <i>Physical Foundations of Cosmology</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521563984" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-56398-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Physical+Foundations+of+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Mukhanov&amp;rft.aufirst=Viatcheslav&amp;rft.au=Mukhanov%2C+Viatcheslav&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-56398-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPadmanabhan.2C_T.1993">Padmanabhan, T. (1993). <i>Structure formation in the universe</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521424860" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-42486-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Structure+formation+in+the+universe&amp;rft.aulast=Padmanabhan%2C+T.&amp;rft.au=Padmanabhan%2C+T.&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-42486-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Discusses the formation of large-scale structures in detail.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPeacock1998">Peacock, John (1998). <i>Cosmological Physics</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521422701" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-42270-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cosmological+Physics&amp;rft.aulast=Peacock&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft.au=Peacock%2C+John&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-42270-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> An introduction including more on general relativity and quantum field theory than most.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPeebles1993">Peebles, P. J. E. (1993). <i>Principles of Physical Cosmology</i>. Princeton University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691019339" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-01933-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Principles+of+Physical+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Peebles&amp;rft.aufirst=P.+J.+E.&amp;rft.au=Peebles%2C+P.+J.+E.&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-691-01933-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Strong historical focus.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPeebles1980">Peebles, P. J. E. (1980). <i>The Large-Scale Structure of the Universe</i>. Princeton University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691082405" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-08240-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Large-Scale+Structure+of+the+Universe&amp;rft.aulast=Peebles&amp;rft.aufirst=P.+J.+E.&amp;rft.au=Peebles%2C+P.+J.+E.&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-691-08240-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> The classic work on <a href="/wiki/Large_scale_structure" title="Large scale structure" class="mw-redirect">large scale structure</a> and correlation functions.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRees2002">Rees, Martin (2002). <i>New Perspectives in Astrophysical Cosmology</i>. Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521645441" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-64544-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=New+Perspectives+in+Astrophysical+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Rees&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin&amp;rft.au=Rees%2C+Martin&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-64544-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeinberg1971">Weinberg, Steven (1971). <i>Gravitation and Cosmology</i>. John Wiley. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0471925675" class="internal">ISBN 0-471-92567-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Gravitation+and+Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Weinberg&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weinberg%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.pub=John+Wiley&amp;rft.isbn=0-471-92567-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A standard reference for the mathematical formalism.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeinberg2008">Weinberg, Steven (2008). <i>Cosmology</i>. Oxford University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198526822" class="internal">ISBN 0198526822</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cosmology&amp;rft.aulast=Weinberg&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weinberg%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0198526822&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Physical_cosmology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
